records.addlTxt:
Defendant Demetrius A Alford in court, in custody, with attorney Katie B. Kegel.   Kevin Michael Osborne appeared for the State of Wisconsin.
Defendant entered a plea of no contest to Count 1 and a plea of guilty to Count 8 with the 2 penalty enhancers on count 8 stricken. Court found defendant guilty of Counts 1 and 8 and orders the 2 penalty enhancers stricken (dismissed).
Counts 2, 3, 4, 5, 6, 7, 9 and 10 along with case 15CM1340 dismissed and read-in.
Defendant's stepfather, mother, Jackie Love and sister, Nicole B. provided statements to the court.

The Defendant was sentenced to the following:

COUNT 1

IMPOSED SENTENCE of: 

5 1/2 YEARS IMPRISONMENT (CREDIT - 206 days)
  -  3 YEARS MONTHS OF INITIAL CONFINEMENT
  -  2 YEARS 6 MONTHS OF EXTENDED SUPERVISION;


RESTITUTION:  $340.00 Buy Money to Metro Drug Unit to be paid as a condition of sentence - restitution to be paid before costs or fines;

COURT COSTS:  $268.00 to be paid as a condition of sentence;

DNA SURCHARGE:  $250.00 to be paid as a condition of sentence;


COUNT 8

5 YEARS PROBATION WITHHELD CONSECUTIVE TO COUNT 1

COURT COSTS:  $268.00 to be paid as a condition of sentence;

DNA SURCHARGE:  $250.00 to be paid as a condition of sentence;

CONDITIONS OF PROBATION/EXTENDED SUPERVISION FOR BOTH COUNTS 1 AND 8:  
*AODA Assessment and follow through with any treatment recommended;
*No Use or Possession of alcohol, controlled substances or drug paraphernalia.
*No Use or Possession of prescription drugs without a valid prescription;
*Any valid prescription drugs must be taken only in the manner in which they are prescribed.
*Inform Agent of all prescriptions
*Follow through with any treatment and/or counseling recommended by Agent;
*Maintain employment and/or combination of schooling;
*Defendant to provide DNA sample, if not yet provided, immediately if in custody otherwise within (3) business days at the Waukesha County Sheriff Department.
*No operation of a motor vehicle without a valid license.

Defendant is eligible for Challenge Incarceration Program.
Defendant is eligible for Substance Abuse Program.

Felony warnings, voting rights and firearms warnings given.

Non-compliance with W.C.S.
Branch 5 ONLY;
Code 1.
